4 X
as long as greatest breadth. Lorum well sclerotised, approximately 0.33 X as long as cardo. Labrum 2.5 X as broad as long ( 38 : 15 ), apical margin almost straight. Mandible 2.5 X as long as basal depth, subapical tooth long. Clypeus slightly longer than broad ( 52 : 50 ), slightly more than lower one quarter extending beyond lower ocular tangent, lacking median longitudinal groove (
Fig. 15 C
